DESCRIPTION:This panel discussion will examine the economic prospects of Ir
 an in a potential post-Islamic Republic transition. Experts will discuss im
 mediate economic stabilization challenges\, medium- and long-term economic 
 planning\, and policy frameworks being developed by Iranian policy groups\,
  including a critical analysis of the Iran Prosperity Project.\n\n \n\nThe 
 discussion will be introduced by Claudia Yaghoobi\, Director of the UNC Cen
 ter for Middle East and Islamic Studies and moderated by Mehdi Shadmehr\, p
 rofessor in the UNC Department of Public Policy. Panelists include: Mohamma
 d Jahan-Parvar\, a DC-based economist\, Mehdi Beyhaghi\, a DC-based economi
 st\, Borghan Narajabad\, a DC-based economist\, and Soroush Ghazi Kalahroud
 i of the University of Alabama.
DTEND:20260309T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
