DESCRIPTION:As the 2026 election cycle approaches\, polls will once again d
 ominate headlines and shape public discussion. This half-day course provide
 s a practical foundation in the design\, analysis\, and communication of el
 ection polls. Topics include questionnaire design\, the advantages and limi
 tations of different survey modes\, weighting techniques to improve represe
 ntativeness\, strategies for likely voter screens\, and approaches to asses
 s\, interpret\, and communicate poll results accurately. Registration and f
 ee (refundable for students) are required for Zoom link access.
