BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:With Matthew Johnson\, Director\, E.L. Reed Herbarium\, Texas T
 ech University\n\n \n\nThursday\, March 12\, 2026\n\n12:00 PM-1:00 PM ET\n\
 nHybrid - Join us in person or on Zoom!\n\nFree\; preregistration required.
  Register >\n\n \n\nHow can plants that have been dead for 50 years help us
  learn how plants acclimated to climate change? Just as historians can lear
 n about our past through newspapers and books\, botanists can use carefully
  preserved herbarium specimens to learn how plants experienced their enviro
 nment when they were still alive. Our team at the E.L. Reed Herbarium at Te
 xas Tech University is using specimens from the 1970s collected in Guadalup
 e Mountains National Park\, a biodiversity hotspot with many rare and endem
 ic plant species. We compared herbarium specimens to new collections to rev
 eal how plants have responded to fifty years of climate and land use change
  through morphology (stomatal densities)\, physiology (stable carbon isotop
 es)\, and genetics (high-throughput DNA sequencing).\n\n \n\nABOUT THE SPEA
 KER\n\nMatt Johnson is an Associate Professor in Biological Sciences and Di
 rector of the E.L. Reed Herbarium at Texas Tech University. He received a P
 hD from Duke University\, where he studied the evolution of reproductive su
 ccess in Sphagnum peatmosses\, and completed post-doctoral work on the Moss
  Tree of Life Project at the Chicago Botanic Garden. His current research f
 ocuses on the origin and maintenance of biodiversity in plants through the 
 development of new tools for phylogenetics and conservation genetics\, and 
 the integration of herbarium specimens into modern botanical research.
DTEND:20260312T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
DTSTART:20260312T160000Z
GEO:35.899603;-79.03247
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Hybrid Lunchbox Talk:  The Botanical Time Machine: 50 Years of Accl
 imation in the Guadalupe Mountains
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52250895000503
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/hybrid-lunchbox-talk-the-botanical-time-
 machine
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This workshop covers the basic features of Lean Library Workspa
 ce (fka: Sciwheel)\, a tool available for free through UNC\, that can be us
 ed to organize and annotate references\, and create citations and bibliogra
 phies. It will focus on setting up your Lean Library Workspace account\, us
 ing Lean Library Workspace to organize and annotate references\, and genera
 ting citations and bibliographies in Word. It is structured for new to begi
 nning users.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences Li
 brary and led by Matti Kauftheil.
DTEND:20260312T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
DTSTART:20260312T180000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Lean Library Workspace (Sciwheel): Create Citations and Bibliograph
 ies
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52134530644421
