BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Exhibits
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Sunday\, March 22\, at 4:00 pm at Coker Arboretum to
  meet the artists of Murmuration\, Jonathon Kirk and Lee Weisert\, and part
 icipate in an open discussion about their process. Reserve your free ticket
 s here: https://forms.gle/4rjnzPbwi4JkFgBa7\n\n \n\nNext in “Rounding Home\
 ,” its eighteenth season\, the Process Series is excited to present Murmura
 tion\, an outdoor soundscape installation by Jonathon Kirk and Lee Weisert.
 \n\n \n\nThe performance features one hundred wirelessly-controlled robotic
  woodblocks spread throughout the trees of Coker Arboretum\, creating a sou
 ndscape that blurs the lines between the sounds of nature and music. The pr
 oject was originally commissioned by the North Carolina Arts Council\, rece
 iving additional funding from New Music USA\, and has recently been present
 ed at the South Carolina Botanical Garden in Clemson and the State Arboretu
 m of Virginia in Boyce\, VA.\n\n \n\nAccording to Weisert\, “The piece expl
 ores the possibilities of physical scale and complexity in an artistic list
 ening experience.” A wide variety of textures\, waves\, and gestures remini
 scent of the natural sound sources they blend with—from chirping birds in t
 he treetops to the crunching leaves beneath your feet—are generated in real
  time using tree-mounted woodblocks and computer programming. Describing th
 e process behind the project\, Weisert offers\, “We are curious to discover
  to what extent music composition can ‘disappear’ into its surroundings. Wh
 at role do proximity and distance play in our musical perception and interp
 retation? How closely can musical form and natural phenomena coexist?”\n\n 
 \n\nHe adds\, “The piece will hopefully act as a kind of sonic prism for re
 discovering Coker Arboretum\,” originally established in 1903\, “which can 
 be easily forgotten within the frenetic activity of campus life.”\n\n \n\nQ
 uestions? Contact us at uncprocessseries@gmail.com or visit our website at 
 https://www.processseries.unc.edu/current-season/murmuration
DTEND:20260322T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
DTSTART:20260322T200000Z
GEO:35.913457;-79.048615
LOCATION:Coker Arboretum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Murmuration: Meet the Artists and Open Discussion
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52277779353028
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/murmuration-meet-the-artists-and-open-di
 scussion
END:VEVENT
