BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:From millions of camera trap photos to satellite imagery tracki
 ng deforestation to corporate climate pledges\, vast amounts of environment
 al data exist but remain effectively invisible until AI helps us see the pa
 tterns within. This panel explores how artificial intelligence is illuminat
 ing hidden stories in nature\, revealing which species are declining\, expo
 sing where forests are disappearing\, and making climate accountability tra
 nsparent. Angel Hsu illuminates how data transforms environmental policy\; 
 Roland Kays tracks wildlife movement through cutting-edge telemetry\, camer
 a trap photos and computer vision\; and Dan Morris accelerates biodiversity
  surveys through Google AI’s nature programs. Together\, they reveal how ar
 tificial intelligence is rewriting our understanding of the natural world. 
 Our speakers will discuss the promise and limitations of using AI to see wh
 at we’re missing\, and how these insights will offer new benefits to societ
 y.\n\n \n\nThis virtual panel will feature:\n\nAngel Hsu\, UNC Chapel Hill 
 and the Data-Driven EnviroLabRoland Kays\, NC State and the NC Museum of Na
 tural SciencesDan Morris\, Google AI for Nature and SocietyModerator\, Beck
 y Boyles\, RENCI at UNC Chapel Hill\n\nWe welcome attendees to join us onli
 ne via Zoom.
DTEND:20260324T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
DTSTART:20260324T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:How AI Reveals Hidden Stories in Nature | Illuminating AI
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52383498999852
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/how-ai-reveals-hidden-stories-in-nature-
 illuminating-ai
END:VEVENT
