BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:As artificial intelligence becomes increasingly woven into teac
 hing\, learning and research\, questions about academic integrity are more 
 timely and more complex than ever. Join students\, faculty and the director
  of UNC's Office of Student Conduct for a thoughtful\, balanced conversatio
 n about how AI is shaping academic work\, where opportunities and risks lie
 \, and how our shared values can guide responsible use. Audience questions 
 and participation are encouraged.\n\n \n\nThis is an in‑person only panel t
 aking place in the Wilson Library (Pleasants Family Assembly Room) and will
  include opportunities for Q&A\, discussion\, and networking.\n\n \n\nPanel
 ists:\n\nModerator: Carrie Baldwin-SoRelle\, UNC University LibraryJenny Ma
 ldonado-Castro\, Undergraduate Student\, UNC Department of CommunicationRei
  Sanchez-Arias\, Teaching Associate Professor and Faculty Director for Mast
 er of Applied Data Science\, UNC School of Data Science and SocietyJenni Sp
 angenberg\, Director of UNC Office of Student ConductDaniel Westreich\, Pro
 fessor\, Gillings School of Global Public HealthMatthew Zuniga\, Graduate S
 tudent\, UNC School of Education \n\nThis event is offered by the Universit
 y Library and the Centre for Faculty Excellence. You can register through t
 he library calendar.
DTEND:20260324T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025640Z
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
GEO:35.90984;-79.050769
LOCATION:Wilson Library \, Pleasants Family Assembly Room (2nd floor\, Wils
 on Library)
SEQUENCE:0
