CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Curious about how designing and making help us think\, learn\, 
 and teach?\n\n \n\nThe Carolina Seminar on Artistic Work in Education invit
 es all UNC staff\, faculty\, and graduate students to Creating as Making: T
 abletop Game Design. In this hands-on workshop\, participants will design a
  tabletop game through a guided activity grounded in the principles of desi
 gn\, iteration\, and making. The session is led by Professor Keith Sawyer\,
  a leading creativity researcher and author of 20 books\, including Learnin
 g to See: Inside the World’s Leading Art and Design Schools. This workshop 
 is based on a project he developed for his fall 2025 UNC course\, "The Make
 r Movement and Education."\n\n \n\nNo prior game design experience required
 . This workshop promises to be a playful and creative afternoon filled with
  conversation. \n\n \n\nSpace is limited — registration required.
