BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Screening
DESCRIPTION:Brazilian Renaissance - 1st Brazilian Cinema Series: As part of
  a semester-long event\, we are launching our first Brazilian cinema series
 . Through this initiative\, we aim to expand awareness and recognition of B
 razilian cultural production\, including its cinema\, which offers audience
 s around the world a glimpse into Brazil's unique artistic identity.\n\nIn 
 recent years\, Brazilian cinema has been drawing growing attention from aud
 iences worldwide. For this event\, we will focus on two contemporary films.
  For the first screening on March 27th\, we will watch the film: I'm Still 
 Here (Walter Salles\, 2024) and for the second screening April 15th: Bacura
 u (Kleber Mendonça Filho and Juliano Dornelles\, 2019). \n\nThrough these s
 creenings\, students will have the opportunity to engage with the work of s
 ome of the most well-known filmmakers in the recent years in Brazil. At the
  end of the events\, students will be able to participate on discussion abo
 ut the films or/and about Brazilian culture.\n\nThe films will be introduce
 d by Dr. Nilzimar Vieira and a student from the Portuguese Program\, who wi
 ll provide cultural and historical context for each film. After the films\,
  students will have the opportunity to exchange questions and share their v
 iews\, building on connections with other films they have seen or with topi
 cs explored in other courses/or from lived experiences. This event invites 
 students to explore Brazilian culture while expanding their understanding o
 f the world and consolidating their intercultural competence. \n\nThis is a
 lso an opportunity for self-reflection.  Students will reflect on questions
  of identity and lived experience. Through the selected films\, we will als
 o learn how Brazilian cinema uses allegory to address social and political 
 critique. Following each film\, we will open for discussion and will create
  space where varied perspectives can be heard from our students\, faculty\,
  and community.
DTEND:20260328T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260327T210000Z
GEO:35.90985;-79.05076
LOCATION:Dey Hall\, Toy Lounge 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:“The Brazilian Renaissance” 1st Brazilian Cinema Series: Film: I'm 
 Still Here (Walter Salles\, 2024)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52324064737495
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/the-brazilian-renaissance-1st-brazilian-
 cinema-series-film-im-still-here-walter-salles-2024
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Performances
DESCRIPTION:FEATURING\n\ncounter)induction\n\nIn its twenty years of virtuo
 sic performances and daring programming\, the composer/performer collective
  counter)induction has established itself as a force of excellence in conte
 mporary music. Hailed by The New York Times for its “fiery ensemble virtuos
 ity” and for its “first-rate performances” by The Washington Post\, c)i has
  given critically-acclaimed performances at Miller Theatre\, Merkin Concert
  Hall\, the Philadelphia Chamber Music Society\, Music at the Anthology\, C
 asa Italiana\, and The George Washington University.\n\nEver since its ince
 ption twenty years ago\, c)i’s mission has been straightforward: world-clas
 s performances of contemporary chamber music\, without hype and without age
 nda other than a complete commitment to the most compelling music of our da
 y.\n\n \n\nPROGRAM\n\nTBA\n\n \n\nPARKING\n\nPlease plan to arrive early as
  parking on campus can be tricky. Learn more about parking and directions t
 o UNC-Chapel Hill’s campus.\n\n \n\nThis performance is part of the 2025-20
 26 Conversations in Modern Music series and is funded by the Jaroslav F. an
 d Barbara S. Hulka Fund for Music in the Chapel Hill community.
DTEND:20260328T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260327T233000Z
GEO:35.912607;-79.053261
LOCATION:Hill Hall\, James and Susan Moeser Auditorium 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:counter)induction | CMM 25-26
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50569353691046
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/counterinduction-cmm-25-26
END:VEVENT
