BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Exhibits
DESCRIPTION:Department of Art and Art History\n\nHonk Honk!!!!\n\nReception
 : March 31\, 2026 5-7 pm\n\n \n\nKillian Bryant (b. 2003\, Durham\, NC) is 
 an artist whose work explores clowning personas and their community\, captu
 ring the playfulness and joy found in their performativity through portrait
 ure\, printmaking\, painting\, puppetry\, and installation. Clowning is an 
 inherently queer art form that invites performers and viewers alike to brea
 k social norms and challenge existing power structures. Through play and ca
 mp sensibilities\, Killian’s practice blurs the lines of social convention\
 , embracing these strategies as forms of resistance and protest. \n\n \n\nI
 n 2026\, Bryant will receive their BFA in Studio Art and BA in Art History 
 at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.\n\n \n\nArtist Instagra
 m: @kebryant.art\n\nArt and Art History website: art.unc.edu\n\n \n\nContac
 t: kbryant5963@gmail.com \n\n \n\nAdmission: Free\n\nGallery Hours: Monday-
 Friday\, 8 am-5 pm
DTEND:20260330T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260330T120000Z
