 ring the playfulness and joy found in their performativity through portrait
 ure\, printmaking\, painting\, puppetry\, and installation. Clowning is an 
 inherently queer art form that invites performers and viewers alike to brea
 k social norms and challenge existing power structures. Through play and ca
 mp sensibilities\, Killian’s practice blurs the lines of social convention\
 , embracing these strategies as forms of resistance and protest. \n\n \n\nI
 n 2026\, Bryant will receive their BFA in Studio Art and BA in Art History 
