BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Interested in computational neuroscience?\nJoin us for a virtua
 l panel featuring researchers from leading institutions as they share their
  paths into the field\, the skills that matter most\, and what it’s like to
  work at the intersection of neuroscience\, data science\, and computation.
 \n\n \n\nPanelists will give brief introductions to their backgrounds and r
 esearch\, followed by a moderated Q&A and a live audience Q&A. This is a gr
 eat opportunity to learn how to get involved in computational neuroscience 
 as an undergraduate\, explore different career paths\, and ask your questio
 ns directly to researchers.\n\n \n\nAll interested students are welcome!\n\
 n \n\nFriday\, April 3\n\n6:30–7:30 PM\n\nLocation: Zoom\n\nCLE credit\n\n 
 \n\nPanelists:\n\nDr. Ceyda Sayali (Johns Hopkins)\n\nNeuroimaging • Psyche
 delics • Cognition & mood\n\n \n\nDr. Alexander Huth (UC Berkeley)\n\nLangu
 age processing • fMRI • Neural network models\n\n \n\nDr. Helena Liu (Princ
 eton\; incoming University of Toronto)\n\nLearning & decision-making • Comp
 utational modeling\n\n \n\nDr. Kilian Pohl (Stanford)\n\nNeuropsychiatry • 
 Neuroimaging • Computational Modeling\n\n \n\nDr. Anandita De (University o
 f Oregon)\n\nNeural population dynamics • Circuit manipulation • Behavior\n
 \n \n\nDr. Aran Nayebi (Carnegie Mellon)\n\nNeuroAI • Machine learning • AI
  safety & society
DTEND:20260403T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260403T223000Z
