BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:As organizations grow\, operational complexity grows with them.
  AI is increasingly helping teams manage that complexity — from streamlinin
 g workflows to improving decision-making and reducing operational friction.
  In this session\, Aaron Purcell\, Managing Director of Emerging Products &
  Solutions and Digital Innovation Leader at KPMG\, will explore how AI-enab
 led tools are helping organizations rethink how work gets done\, optimize p
 rocesses\, and build systems that scale alongside evolving demands.\n\n \n\
 nEnjoy a complimentary Meantime coffee during the event\, and stick around 
 afterward for casual networking over fresh Brandwein’s bagels\, courtesy of
  Innovate Carolina. It’s a chance to continue the conversation\, exchange i
 deas\, and make new connections in the café.
DTEND:20260407T143000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260407T130000Z
GEO:35.914361;-79.054904
LOCATION:Innovate Carolina Junction
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Run Smarter: How AI Supports Growth and Operational Efficiency
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52330173226233
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/run-smarter-how-ai-supports-growth-and-o
 perational-efficiency
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill School of Socia
 l Work is pleased to welcome Maxine Eichner as the guest speaker for the 20
 26 annual Bobby Boyd Leadership Lecture Series on April 7\, 2026.\n\n \n\nE
 ichner’s lecture examines how the United States came to expect so much of f
 amilies with so little public support\, and how this gap has led overwhelmi
 ng numbers of poor and disproportionately Black families to be trapped in t
 he nation’s child welfare system. She traces how policy has come to emphasi
 ze family responsibility without parallel investment in the conditions that
  make children’s welfare truly possible\, while calling to build systems th
 at meet families earlier and to align policy with what children and familie
 s need to flourish.\n\n \n\nEichner is the Graham Kenan Distinguished Profe
 ssor of Law at UNC School of Law. She is both a lawyer and political scient
 ist. She writes on issues of families and inequality\; U.S. social welfare 
 law and policy\; and the relationship of the family\, the workplace\, and m
 arket forces. She is the author of The Free-Market Family: How the Market C
 rushed the American Dream (and How It Can Be Restored) (OUP\, 2020)\, and T
 he Supportive State: Families\, Government\, and America’s Political Ideals
  (OUP\, 2010).\n\n \n\nThis event will be presented virtually and in person
  in the auditorium of the Tate-Turner-Kuralt Building on UNC’s campus. The 
 presentation starts at 12:30 p.m. and is free and open to the public. Parti
 cipants are required to register for the event. A free lunch will be held i
 n the TTK lobby for attendees beginning at 11:30 a.m.
DTEND:20260407T174500Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260407T163000Z
GEO:35.907102;-79.054247
LOCATION:Tate-Turner-Kuralt Building\, Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:2026 Bobby Boyd Leadership Lecture
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52249837495298
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/2026-bobby-boyd-leadership-lecture
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:The 42nd Annual Zollicoffer Lecture is an annual event that hig
 hlights the healthcare needs of communities across the state of North Carol
 ina and the importance of pursuing innovative solutions to serve our commun
 ities.\n\n \n\nThe Office of Medical Student Education\, Curricular Pathway
 s invites students\, faculty\, staff\, and community members to attend the 
 42nd Annual Zollicoffer Lecture on Tuesday\, April 7\, 2026\, at 12:30 PM i
 n the Roper Hall Active Learning Theater (Roper 1101).\n\n \n\nThis annual 
 event highlights the healthcare needs of communities across the state of No
 rth Carolina and the importance of pursuing innovative solutions to serve o
 ur communities. This year’s featured speaker is Dr. Kenya McNeal-Trice\, Vi
 ce President for Board Relations of the American Board of Pediatrics\; Dist
 inguished Professor and former Senior Vice Chair of Education in the Depart
 ment of Pediatrics at the University of North Carolina (UNC) School of Medi
 cine.\n\n \n\nA nationally recognized leader in academic medicine and pedia
 trics\, Dr. McNeal-Trice’s advocacy has inspired change and earned her nume
 rous awards as a mentor\, educator\, and champion for children and families
 . As a pediatrician with a clinical focus on hospital medicine\, child malt
 reatment\, and mental and behavioral health\, Dr. McNeal-Trice thrives in c
 linical settings requiring the management of children presenting with compl
 ex medical findings. She prioritizes teamwork to achieve desired health out
 comes while promoting family-centered care\, collaborative practice\, and p
 atient advocacy.\n\n \n\nThe lecture is open to all students\, faculty\, st
 aff\, and community members interested in healthcare.
DTEND:20260407T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260407T163000Z
GEO:35.906358;-79.051675
LOCATION:Roper Hall\, Active Learning Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:42nd Annual Zollicoffer Lecture
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52118390077287
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/42nd-annual-zollicoffer-lecture
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Want to know how generative AI (GenAI) can be used to support y
 our research? This workshop covers various GenAI tools that have applicatio
 ns for research tasks including tools that support writing manuscripts\, ex
 ploring and summarizing literature (e.g.\, Research Rabbit\, Consensus\, an
 d Elicit)\, performing evidence synthesis (including systematic and scoping
  reviews)\, and data analysis. An overview of library resources that suppor
 t GenAI including the Library AI Studio is also provided.\n\n \n\nThis work
 shop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences Library and led by Matti Kaufthe
 il.
DTEND:20260407T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260407T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Leveraging Generative AI for Research Tasks
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52134585573126
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/leveraging-generative-ai-for-research-ta
 sks-4439
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:The Clinical and Translational Science (CTS) Pilot Program at N
 C TraCS is now accepting applications for our CTS Pilot Awards. These award
 s support projects that advance translational science—the field focused on 
 understanding the scientific and operational principles that underlie each 
 step of the translational process—with up to $50\,000 in direct costs for a
  period of one year.\n\n \n\nNC TraCS is holding information sessions via Z
 oom for investigators interested in learning more about this funding opport
 unity. Topics covered during the session include:\n\nWhat is Translational 
 Science as distinct from Translational Research?Application procedure\, inc
 luding required application components\, important dates and contact inform
 ationProgram-specific grantsmanship tipsQ&ARFA and additional information: 
 https://tracs.unc.edu/pilot\n\n \n\nRegister for an upcoming Information Se
 ssion:\n\nApril 7\, 2026 4-5 p.m. | go.unc.edu/Apr7pilot\nApril 13\, 2026 3
 -4 p.m. | go.unc.edu/Apr13pilot\n\n \n\nPresenters\nDavid Peden\, MD\, MS\n
 Director\, CTS Pilot Program\nNC TraCS Institute\n\n \n\nDavid Carroll\, Ph
 D\nDirector\, Research Funding Development\nNC TraCS Institute\n\n \n\nKait
 lin Zalcikova\, PhD\nProgram Manager\, CTS Pilot Program\nNC TraCS Institut
 e
DTEND:20260407T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260407T200000Z
