DESCRIPTION:Carolina Alumni invites all seniors to climb the Bell Tower. Th
 anks to the generous support of more than 61\,000 Carolina Alumni members\,
  we are thrilled to extend this tradition to seniors during Senior Week. We
  will allow climbing after 9 a.m. We will close the line at 4 p.m. All seni
 ors in line by 4 p.m. will be allowed to climb. This is a first-come\, firs
 t-served event.\n\nDon’t miss out on all of the excitement: Enjoy the first
  drop of the Carolina Alumni Review Senior Edition\, grab some tasty bites 
 from food trucks\, have fun with music and games\, and take home exclusive 
 swag and discounts. Play a round of cornhole and snap some fun memories at 
 the photo booth. Plus\, there will be exciting giveaways throughout the day
 .\n\nClass of ’26 Senior Edition: Campus distribution starts at this event\
 , Wednesday\, April 8\, during the Bell Tower Climb. Details. Senior T-shir
 ts will also be for sale during this event.\n\nThe Morehead-Patterson Bell 
 Tower is one of our favorite campus landmarks. Climbing the Bell Tower with
  Carolina Alumni adds 256 steps to your day (128 going up\, 128 coming down
 ). From ground to the fourth floor landing\, you can say “I climbed the Bel
 l Tower.” Check out facts about the Bell Tower.
DTEND:20260408T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
