BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Engagement in Research Nuts & Bolts: Specific Approaches for En
 gaging Patient & Community Partners in Research\n\n \n\nThere is no "one-si
 ze-fits-all" approach to engaging patient\, community\, or other partners i
 n your research. Rather\, there are a variety of engagement methods to suit
  your study's needs\, your research team's capacity\, and your partners' in
 terests.\n\n \n\nThis online training will describe three common approaches
  for working with patient\, community\, and other partners in your research
 : 1) consultative community feedback sessions\; 2) advisory boards\; and 3)
  sustained collaboration with partners as members of the research team.\n\n
  \n\nThe session will cover considerations for choosing these specific enga
 gement methods\, as well as concrete processes and steps for implementing e
 ach approach. Participation in our Engagement in Research 101 training is n
 ot required to attend this session\; however\, some knowledge of engagement
 \, whether from prior training(s) or personal experience\, may foster deepe
 r understanding of the material in this session.\n\n \n\nPresenters:\nAlici
 a Bilheimer\, MPH - Director of Engaged Science\, NC TraCS\nVeronica Carlis
 le\, MPH\, CHES - Senior Community Health Educator\, UNC Lineberger Compreh
 ensive Cancer Center (LCCC)\nNisha Datta\, MS - Senior Project Manager\, NC
  TraCS\nSimone Frank\, MPH - Senior Project Manager\, NC TraCS\nJennifer Po
 tter\, MPH\, CHES - Senior Program Coordinator for Clinical Outreach\, LCCC
 \n\n \n\nRegister\n\n \n\nEngaging Patient\, Community\, and Other Partners
  in Your Research is a multi-part online training series. You may register 
 for the entire series OR any single training session. This training series 
 was developed collaboratively with patient\, community\, and researcher par
 tners and is co-sponsored by the UNC Lineberger Comprehensive Cancer Center
  and NC TraCS Institute.
DTEND:20260415T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260415T140000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Engagement in Research Nuts & Bolts: Specific Approaches for Engagi
 ng Patient & Community Partners in Research
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52319587074644
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/engagement-in-research-nuts-bolts-specif
 ic-approaches-for-engaging-patient-community-partners-in-research-2624
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Over the past few years\, employees have been asked to do more\
 , do their work differently and do better in new and challenging ways\, all
  while managing family life and personal responsibilities that seem never-e
 nding. The feeling of languishing or “will this ever end?” abounds througho
 ut the workforce and can have a huge impact on your mental health. Working 
 on our mental health need not be reserved just for those who are in crisis 
 or who are faced with an official diagnosis: Mental health matters for ever
 yone. This interactive session provides more details and helpful ideas on h
 ow to move from languishing through work and life to flourishing.\n\n \n\nW
 orkshop Objectives\nThis training will help you:\n• Understand the concepts
  of languishing and flourishing\n• Reflect on your current mental wellness 
 status\n• Describe three concrete approaches to move from languishing to fl
 ourishing\n• Identify and action plan to implement within the next 30 days 
 to move toward flourishing\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration li
 nk and select the “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260415T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260415T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Languishing\, Flourishing\, and Your Mental Health
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375348301456
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/languishing-flourishing-and-your-mental-
 health-518
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join us online for an overview of coursework\, practicum\, fina
