DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in developing professional skills to help yo
 u succeed in global careers?\n\n \n\nThe Diplomacy Initiative Forum on Skil
 ls in Global Careers brings Carolina alumni to Chapel Hill to support stude
 nts in exploring global career pathways and cultivating the skills necessar
 y to work in global affairs. Participate in the policy brief competition\, 
 resume reviews and alumni discussions to gain a deeper understanding of the
  competencies required in global affairs while developing and refining prof
 essional skills essential for success.\n\n \n\nCLE credit is available for 
 the Policy Brief Competition awards ceremony and the global tech discussion
 . Activities can count for the Carolina Diplomacy Fellows program.\n\n \n\n
 Policy Brief Competition\n\nTo submit to this year’s competition\, please v
 isit the 2026 Policy Brief Competition webpage. Submissions are due by Apri
 l 8 at 4 p.m.\n\n \n\nWednesday\, April 15\n\nPolicy Brief Competition awar
 ds ceremony5:30 p.m.\, FedEx Global Education Center\, Nelson Mandela Audit
 oriumCarolina students are stepping up to take on global challenges like cl
 imate change\, cybersecurity and migration through compelling policy briefs
  with innovative solutions. Celebrate the finalists of this year’s Policy B
 rief Competition at the awards ceremony. Hear from winners as they present 
 their briefs\, gain insights from the competition’s judges — five alumni wh
 o bring global affairs expertise from their accomplished careers — and lear
 n how complex transnational crises demand multifaceted approaches\, and wha
 t skills you can hone as you prepare for a career in policymaking. See alum
 ni judges’ bios below!Alumni networking reception6:30 p.m.\, FedEx Global E
 ducation Center\, fourth floor After the awards ceremony\, join Carolina st
 udents\, faculty\, staff and alumni interested in global affairs for the an
 nual networking reception. Meet professionals and peers and hear about thei
 r experiences and careers to learn about opportunities to chart your path t
 o a career in global affairs.RSVP to secure your spot for the ceremony and 
 reception! \n\nThursday\, April 16\n\nResume review session: National secur
 ity9:30-11:30 a.m.\, FedEx Global Education Center\, room 2008/2010 (second
  floor conference room) Want to sharpen your federal resume for opportuniti
 es in national security? Sign up for a 10-minute slot to meet individually 
 with Ned Kelly ’05 from the Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA). Kelly will r
 eview your resume and offer tips to strengthen it. Please bring a hard copy
  with you and dress professionally.Resume review session: General9:30-11:30
  a.m.\, FedEx Global Education Center\, room 2008/2010 (second floor confer
 ence room)Looking for general resume advice for global careers? Sign up for
