 y with the U.S. Department of Commerce. Srivastava will review your resume 
 and offer tips to strengthen it. Please bring a hard copy with you and dres
 s professionally.“Careers in Business Diplomacy: Global Tech Policy in the 
 Age of AI”11 a.m.-12 p.m.\, FedEx Global Education Center\, room 3009 (DeBe
 rry Board Room)Speak with Carolina alumnus and technology and science polic
 y expert\, Jeffrey Brown\, about the intersections of global policy\, busin
 ess and technology. Brown has a range of global policy experiences from pub
 lic to private sectors in the U.S. and abroad. Hear from Brown on his caree
 r path and advice for students entering the global policy field. Come ready
  to ask questions! RSVP to secure your spot! \n\nAlumni judges\n\nJeffrey B
 rown ’15 (M.A.)Jennifer Davis ’94\, ’97 (JD)Ned Kelly ’05Justin Sosne ’06Ja
 tin Srivastava ’23
