BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:Curious about what data science and AI bring to your life every
 day? Join us for an evening discussing exciting local research from scienti
 sts at the NC Museum of Natural Sciences\, UNC-Chapel Hill\, UNC’s Renaissa
 nce Computing Institute (RENCI)\, NC State University\, and beyond! You’ll 
 learn about exciting research using artificial intelligence and data scienc
 e methods to spark charismatic animal research\, health-related research\, 
 participatory science opportunities in your backyard and across the globe i
 n Galapagos\, Puerto Rico\, and beyond. The highlight of the evening will b
 e the Science Cafe talk and its relevance to your daily life. You’ll leave 
 the evening knowing how artificial intelligence benefits Museum research\, 
 art\, and the world around us.\n \n\nJoin us in person or watch the livestr
 eam of the Science Café beginning at 7:00 PM.\n \n\nEvent Schedule\n\n6:00p
 m-7:00pm: Meet local scientists and interact with themed exhibits to learn 
 about their exciting research\n\n7:00pm-8:00pm\, Science Cafe: Illuminating
  Artificial Intelligence: Using AI to increase the value of Museum specimen
 s\n \n\nOur evening keynote pairs Dr. Chris Bizon\, Director of Data Scienc
 e and Analytics at RENCI and Dr. Lily Hughes\, Research Curator of Ichthyol
 ogy at the NC Museum of Natural Sciences and Research Assistant Professor a
 t NC State University\, highlighting how artificial intelligence illuminate
 s our understanding of the Museum’s ichthyology collections.
DTEND:20260417T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025641Z
DTSTART:20260416T220000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
