BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Strengthening Engagement in Research: Building and Maintaining 
 Relationships with Patient & Community Partners\n\n \n\nMeaningful partners
 hips with patients\, community members\, or other collaborators involved in
  your research are invaluable. Projects are set up for success when care is
  intentionally given to developing and strengthening partnerships over time
 .\n\n \n\nThis online training will describe best practices for building mu
 tually beneficial partnerships. The session will also cover common challeng
 es that researchers and patient\, community\, and other partners experience
  when working together\, along with suggested solutions.\n\n \n\nParticipat
 ion in our Engagement in Research 101 or Engagement in Research Nuts and Bo
 lts trainings are not required to attend this session\; however\, some know
 ledge of engagement\, whether from prior training(s) or personal experience
 \, may foster deeper understanding of the material in this session.\n\n \n\
 nPresenters:\nAlicia Bilheimer\, MPH - Director of Engaged Science\, NC Tra
 CS\nVeronica Carlisle\, MPH\, CHES - Senior Community Health Educator\, UNC
  Lineberger Comprehensive Cancer Center (LCCC)\nNisha Datta\, MS - Senior P
 roject Manager\, NC TraCS\nSimone Frank\, MPH - Senior Project Manager\, NC
  TraCS\nJennifer Potter\, MPH\, CHES - Senior Program Coordinator for Clini
 cal Outreach\, LCCC\nMembers of the NC TraCS Community and Patient Advisory
  Board and the UNC Lineberger Community Advisory Board\n\n \n\nRegister\n\n
  \n\nEngaging Patient\, Community\, and Other Partners in Your Research is 
 a multi-part online training series. You may register for the entire series
  OR any single training session. This training series was developed collabo
 ratively with patient\, community\, and researcher partners and is co-spons
 ored by the UNC Lineberger Comprehensive Cancer Center and NC TraCS Institu
 te.
DTEND:20260422T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025642Z
DTSTART:20260422T140000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Strengthening Engagement in Research: Building and Maintaining Rela
 tionships with Patient & Community Partners
