DESCRIPTION:A virtual onboarding series for principal investigators (PIs)\,
  faculty\, and project/program leads across campus. The program offers an i
 ntroductory overview of key responsibilities involved in leading and managi
 ng a research program. Topics will include developing proposal ideas\, subm
 itting proposals\, managing awards through closeout\, and navigating ethics
 \, compliance\, and research security.\n\n \n\nWhile the sessions are espec
 ially valuable for new researchers\, all members of the UNC-CH research com
 munity interested in strengthening their understanding of the research ente
 rprise and their roles within it are encouraged to attend.
