BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This course will be held online only over 3 days (September 14\
 , 16\, and 18). Attendance is required as it will not be recorded.\n\nThis 
 6-hour course provides training on how AI can assist a survey project from 
 beginning to the end.\n\nWe will focus on each step of the research process
  (Callegaro and Yang\, 2025)\n\nPlanningExecutionActivationIn the planning 
 phase there are two sub phases\n1) Ideate and define\n\nAI can be an idea h
 elper and assist on generating research ideas starting from previously know
 ledgeA literature review can definitely be assisted by AI and there are spe
 cific tools available for that2) Design and plan\n\nThe design stage is whe
 re AI can assist in producing design brief\, analysis plan and map the conc
 epts that are going to be measured using the questionnaireThe execution pha
 se consists of\n3) Data wizard\n\nHere AI has been used to help drafting an
 d pretesting the questionnaire\, help writing survey material such as surve
 y invitation and confidentiality assurances.4) Analysis copilot\n\nOnce the
  data collection is under way\, AI can assist in automating\, and writing s
 tatistical code to analyze the dataset (stat code assistant). It can also b
 e used as  theme discovery\, for coding of open ended answers and data visu
 alization.The activation phase consists of:\n5) Insight partner\n\nHelp sum
 marize findings\, generate reports\, help review the final deliverables suc
 h as a research report or a complete academic paper6) Storytelling aid\n\nD
 evelop presentation materials\, create multi-media artifacts\, generated bl
 og post for different platforms\, generate images based on content from the
  researchOrganizational Structure of the Course \nThe course will be taught
  in a workshop style where the lectures will be using presentation slides a
 s a roadmap. After each concept has been introduced and discussed\, the par
 ticipants will be invited to work on brief hands on exercises with differen
 t LLMs such as Gemini\, Claude\, Copilot\, and ChatGPT\n\nParticipants will
  be strongly encouraged to ask questions during lectures\, especially on ho
 w the content relates to their own research.\n\nLearning objectives\nBy the
  end of the course\, you will:\n\nLearn how to prompt LLMs for survey resea
 rch help and assistanceLearn how to evaluate the quality of LLMs outputsStr
 engths and challenges of different LLMs toolsWhere LLMs are not necessaryEt
 hical usage of LLMs/AI ToolsRecent debate of using LLMs to produce research
  and write academic papersRegistration and fee (refundable for UNCCH studen
 ts) are required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260914T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025642Z
DTSTART:20260914T140000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:AI Assisted Surveys
