BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This course introduces participants to constructivist grounded 
 theory (CGT). Grounded theory (GT) methods consist of flexible guidelines t
 o fit particular research problems\, not to apply mechanically. With these 
 guidelines\, you expedite and systematize data collection and analysis. GT 
 methods can assist researchers in making their work more analytic\, precise
 \, and compelling.\n\nIn this course\, following an exploration of the hist
 ory and development of GT\, we examine GT basic guidelines and major strate
 gies\, including initial line-by-line and focused coding\, the use of gerun
 ds\, memoing\, diagramming\, theoretical sampling\, and categorizing. Throu
 ghout the sessions\, there is an emphasis on CGT’s epistemological foundati
 on and resultant adaptations to the research process\, including regarding 
 the literature review\, researcher positionality/ies and reflexivity\, and 
 participant involvement.\n\nThe course will include a number of hands-on ex
 ercises to exemplify\, and give participants an opportunity to practice\, t
 he strategies being discussed. For the coding exercise\, you may bring and 
 use some of your own qualitative data\, or if you do not have data yet\, so
 me will be supplied. Clear guidelines and support are provided to course pa
 rticipants with regard to all aspects of CGT.\n\nThe sessions will utilize 
 CGT readings and resources from Kathy Charmaz\, Robert Thornberg\, Adele Cl
 arke\, and myself\, and will draw on the extensive scholarship of Barney Gl
 aser and Anselm Strauss. A pack of materials will be shared with participan
 ts in advance of the course. This course will be of interest to those doing
  full CGT studies but also to those who may be interested in learning about
  and potentially using some of the powerful GT strategies (such as coding) 
 in studies with a different overall methodological approach.\n\nRegistratio
 n and fee (refundable for UNCCH students) are required for Zoom link access
 .
DTEND:20261013T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T025642Z
DTSTART:20261013T130000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Introduction to Constructivist Grounded Theory
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52259414932087
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/introduction-to-constructivist-grounded-
 theory-5530
END:VEVENT
